<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>come after someone • go after someone</xh5><p> <i>come after someone—</i>pursue or chase a person (in order to attack, arrest, etc.): I heard the clicking noise from the street getting closer. It sounded like they were <u>coming after</u> me.</p><p> <i>go after someone—</i>1. <i>= come after someone: </i>Half the guards <u>went after</u> the escaped prisoners but they got away free. 2. <i>(coll.)</i> make romantic advances: Antonio says Luis is the only one he’d trust because Luis would never <u>go after</u> his girl.</p> </entry>
